On Read Across America Day, the article emphasizes the importance of promoting the joy of reading and literacy. It states that literacy has led to significant discoveries, innovations, and the development of great minds throughout history. The article encourages everyone to remember that children hold the promise of a bright future, and reading is a gift that helps them learn, grow, and explore. It quotes Dr. Seuss, highlighting the idea that reading expands knowledge and opens up new opportunities. The article concludes by reminding readers of their duty to instill a love of reading in future generations.